Web service template plugin for Moodle 2.X (BETA VERSION)
--------------------------------------------------------

It is a webservice designed for moodle to export models Courses into Tangerine Platform.

1) STEPS TO INSTALL:

A) MANUALLY INSTALL PROCEDURE (RECOMMENDED)
///////////
// 1) - Unzip sam.zip and copy all files to local folder (Local Folder is located in the root of moodle Framework )
// 2)- your folder Should look like this /local/sam/externallib.php


B)FROM MOODLE ADMIN:
///////////
// 1)- Install Addon (Admin > Plugins > Install  Addons)
// 2) Choose "Plugin type" = Local Plugin. Browse sam.zip Check mark the Acknowledgement Click on Install

2) CONFIGURATION STEPS (REQUIRED)*:

/// MOODLE ADMINISTRATION SETUP STEPS
// 1- Enable web service advance feature (Admin > Advanced features)
// 2- Enable XMLRPC protocol (Admin > Plugins > Web services > Manage protocols)
// 3- Create a token for a specific user and for the service 'My service SAM' (Admin > Plugins > Web services > Manage tokens)
// 4- Copy The Token and edit client.php from this location <yoursite>/local/sam/client/client.php 
      Search For Word <YOUR TOKEN HERE> and replace it with actual token.( it should look like $token = '456easdfe3fr4f43t3e'; ).
// 5- Run this script directly from your browser: <yoursite>/local/sam/client/client.php